He has written an unusual book, which he does not inappropriately describe as "a work of anti-Semitic history".
It contains only a few big names, important contracts or famous battles. There are hardly ambassadors, frantic reporters or discussions about tactics and equipment.
It is less a book about what happened, he explains, but rather "a book about how it was". It is about "feelings, impressions, experiences and moods".
