Also pay attention to the language of your subject.
The slip of Scott Peterson is famous when he used the past form when he claimed that his killed wife was still alive and triggered a national search for her.
Deceptive persons can also use a distancing language: "I had no sexual relationship with this woman... Miss Lewinsky" or when you repeat a tricky question in the whole.
The most common verbal signs are subtle.
