On the delicate issue of euthanasia and accompanying suicide, the authors of the report come to conclusions which are contrary to the position of the federal government, which has already expressed no intention of amending the law on euthanasia and accompanying suicide.
However, according to experts who have equally inspected all those countries whose approach has legalized or decriminalized euthanasia and accompanying suicide, there is no evidence that such decriminalisation would entail abuses in their application, i.e. the practice of euthanasia or accompanying suicide of uncompetent or unwilling persons.
